4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Existing election law sets forth procedures for
6 state electors to cast votes for the President and Vice
7 President of the United States in accordance with the
8 intention of the voters of the state.
9 This bill would establish procedures in the
10 event a presidential elector fails to vote in
11 accordance with the voters of the state.
